{# Get the brightness value, fallback to 404 if not present 

{Desired Lux A2 (Ex. 500 Lux)} = {500 (desired_brightness)} - {Lux measure by OPT3001} + {Current lux of A2 (Current State)}

Note 
Using led_lux_minolta_t_10a_lux_meter (number template) for map 8 bit value (current state of A2 smart light) into an illuminance, measure by MinoltaT10A lux meter which is a lab grade lux meter from KMUTT Illuminance Laboratory.
#}

{% set input_value = states('input_number.desired_brightness') | int -states('number.opt3001_illuminance_calibrated') | int + states('number.led_lux_minolta_t_10a_lux_meter') | int%}

{# Use namespace so we can modify values inside a loop and keep them #}
{% set ns = namespace(closest_key=table.keys() | list | first, smallest_diff=(input_value - (table.keys() | list | first)) | abs) %}

{% for k in table.keys() %}
  {% set diff = (input_value - k) | abs %}
  {% if diff < ns.smallest_diff %}
    {% set ns.closest_key = k %}
    {% set ns.smallest_diff = diff %}
  {% endif %}
{% endfor %}

{{ table[ns.closest_key] }}